Author: Sunopsis Version: 3.1 Updated: 30-OCT-2002
Knowledge Integration Module Integrates data in any ISO-92 compliant database target table in truncate / insert (append) mode. Data can be controlled. Erroneous data is isolated in the error table and can be recycled.
When using this module with a journalized source table, data should be manually filtered to not include source deletions (add a filter on JRN_FLAG = 'I')
Restrictions: - the TRUNCATE option is not implemented on all RDBMs - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - The FLOW_CONTROL option calls the Knowledge Control Module to isolate the errors. The flow is first stored in the flow table (created dynamically) before performing the control. - When using the RECYCLE_ERRORS option, you have to set an Update Key for your interface.
Check this option if you want to create the target table
Check this option if you want to truncate the target table. Note : this option is not supported on all RDBMS
Check this option if you want to delete all rows
Check this option if you want to insert new data in the target table
Use this option to perform a flow control. You should also select an appropriate Knowledge Control Module (KCM) in your interface.
Check this option to recycle previous errors
Check this option to control the target table after the insert operation
Uncheck this option to not commit your insert operations on your target table. This option is set to true by default.
